correctness.rationale: Several key fields are correct (PEALD method, precursors DADI/TMGa/DEZ, Ar/O2 plasma co-reactant, 200 °C temperature, ~1.2 Torr pressure, 300 W plasma power, substrates, bottom-gate top-contact). However, the extraction has multiple schema violations, null/placeholder values, and factual errors: (1) Growth-per-cycle: the values 3.8/3.23/0.29 were misinterpreted from precursor exposure amounts (nMole or μMole per cm²) in Fig. S1; they are not thickness (Å). Units and quantities are incorrect. (2) Dosing times: reported as seconds in the article (DADI 1.5 s, TMGa 0.1 s, DEZ 0.1 s) but encoded with unit MilliSEC and numeric 1.5/0.1 (implies 1.5 ms/0.1 ms) — wrong by 10^3. (3) Subthreshold swing: given as 0.24 V/dec in the paper, but encoded as 0.24 MilliV — wrong by 10^3 and missing /decade semantics required by the domain. (4) Crystallinity: set to “amorphous,” which contradicts the article showing composition-dependent phases; the optimal region (In ~0.56–0.63) exhibits cubic In2O3 (222) peaks, not amorphous. (5) Composition: atomicRatio fixed at 1:1:1 (XPS) while device metrics correspond to the ‘optimal region’ (XIn 0.56–0.63, XGa 0.13–0.17, XZn 0.17–0.34). Internal inconsistency and not traceable to a specific sample in Table S1. (6) Device metrics mixed: on/off ratio 8.9×10^8 corresponds to IGZO_In_1 (Table S2), while μFE and Vth correspond to the optimal region/IGZO_In_2; values are taken from different samples. (7) Numerous required fields are null or placeholders, violating the ‘no empty/null’ constraint: carrierGas/purgingGas (“Not Found”), reactor.name/manufacturer None, deliveryMethod “Not Found”, thicknessControl.numberofCycles None, nucleationPeriod None, dosingTime.coReactant None, purgeTime.* None, flowRates.* None, supercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles.count None, optical/electrical property values None, uniformity.variation None, conformality.aspectRatio None, filmComposition.elementalConcentration None, filmDensity.value None. (8) Roughness/AFM is asserted though AFM is not reported in the article. Corrections: use correct GPC units/values (or omit if not available), fix dosing and SS units, choose one coherent sample with consistent composition, crystallinity, and device metrics from the paper (e.g., IGZO_In_2), populate film density from XRR for that sample, remove ‘Not Found’/None by either providing article-based values or omitting optional fields, and do not fabricate characterization methods not reported.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains multiple schema violations and factual inconsistencies. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes described in the article (numerous IGZO compositions and supercycles) are collapsed into one process; no separate processes or explicit supercycle counts (n1, n2, n3) are provided. (2) Required numeric fields are left null, violating the schema: thicknessControl.numberofCycles, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime (co-reactant), purgeTime, all flowRates, supercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles.count, materialProperties.uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values, roughness.value, filmDensity.value. (3) GPC values are incorrect: the article reports precursor dose thresholds (3.8 nMole/cm2, 3.23 µMole/cm2, 0.29 µMole/cm2), not growth-per-cycle in Å; the extraction mislabels these as Å. (4) Time units are wrong: precursor dosing times are reported in seconds (DADI 1.5 s, TMGa 0.1 s, DEZ 0.1 s) but encoded as milliseconds with the same numeric values. (5) Device metrics are inconsistent and not traceable to a single sample: mobility (41.4 cm2/Vs), Vth (-0.9 V), SS (0.24 V/dec) are taken from an optimal region, while the on/off ratio (8.9×10^8) corresponds to a different sample (e.g., IGZO_In_1), breaking coherence. SS is also given as 0.24 with a MilliV unit (should be ~240 mV). (6) Crystallinity is set to ‘amorphous’ despite the article reporting composition-dependent phases (amorphous Ga-rich, hexagonal Zn-rich, cubic In2O3 in In-rich). (7) Atomic ratio ‘1:1:1’ is not representative of the reported device-optimal samples and lacks traceability to the selected process. (8) Reactor.name/manufacturer are set to null (type violation); carrier/purging gas are marked “Not Found” though plasma is Ar/O2; deliveryMethod not provided. To improve completeness, add separate processes per composition or clearly specify one sample with consistent, traceable values; populate supercycle a:b:c counts, cycle counts and film thickness; correct units and GPC; fill dosing/purge/plasma exposure/flow rates (or omit optional fields rather than using nulls); provide measured film properties (bandgap, density) and correct crystallinity per sample; and ensure all numeric fields use QUDT-compliant units with non-null values.
